The paper deals with distributed computing, specifically consensus and set consensus protocols, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also makes use of logic-based and knowledge-based analysis, which are topics covered in the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial and topological analysis, which are topics covered in the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories, respectively. Finally, the paper deals with synchronous message-passing contexts with crash failures, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
